    <section class="hero">
      <div>
        <h1>How to Skip Non‑Essential Outside Activities and Focus on Your Online Business</h1>
        <p class="lead">A practical, balanced plan to cut non-productive outside activities, structure focused work time, set up systems, and grow an online business without burning out.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Quick Wins</h3>
          <ul class="check">
            <li>Time‑block your highest‑value work first (90–120 minutes).</li>
            <li>Replace casual outings with short active breaks (walks, stretches).</li>
            <li>Create a simple business plan with weekly milestones.</li>
            <li>Use tools to automate repetitive tasks (scheduling, invoicing).</li>
          </ul>
          <div style="margin-top:10px"><a class="btn" href="#contact">Get the 7‑Day Focus Plan</a></div>
        </div>

        <div id="steps" class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
          <h2>Step‑by‑Step Plan</h2>
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="num">1</div><div><h4>Define Your Why & Goals</h4><p>Write 3 concrete business outcomes for the next 90 days (revenue, audience, product). Clear goals make it easier to decline non-essential activities.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">2</div><div><h4>Audit Your Time</h4><p>Track one week of activities using a simple timer (phone or pomodoro). Identify low-value outings and time drains to reduce or batch.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">3</div><div><h4>Time‑Block & Protect Deep Work</h4><p>Schedule undisturbed blocks (90m) for product, content, or sales. Treat them like appointments — no social visits or errands during these blocks.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">4</div><div><h4>Set Boundaries & Communicate</h4><p>Tell friends/family your new schedule. Offer short windows for calls or meetups so you maintain relationships without losing focus.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">5</div><div><h4>Automate & Delegate</h4><p>Use tools for scheduling, bookkeeping, email autoresponders, and hire freelancers for tasks that take time but add little value.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">6</div><div><h4>Replace, Don't Remove</h4><p>Swap long social outings for energizing short activities: 20–30 minute walks, quick calls, or focused creative sessions to recharge.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">7</div><div><h4>Review Weekly & Adjust</h4><p>Every Sunday, review progress toward goals and adjust which outside activities you keep or pause. Celebrate wins to stay motivated.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
          <h3>Tools & Templates</h3>
          <ul class="check">
            <li>Task & Projects: Trello, Asana, Notion</li>
            <li>Time Tracking: Toggl, Clockify, Pomodoro timers</li>
            <li>Automation: Zapier, Make (Integromat)</li>
            <li>Outsourcing: Upwork, Fiverr</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
